class="db7ee1ac fw6 f4 black-90 dib lh-solid ma0 no-underline hover-black">perstore</h3></a></div><p class="_8fbbd57d f5 black-60 mt1 mb0 pv1 no-underline lh-copy">Perstore is a cross-platform JavaScript object store interface for mapping persistent  objects to various different storage mediums using an interface based on W3C's [IndexedDB object store API](http://www.w3.org/TR/IndexedDB/#object-store-sync) and analogous to the HTTP REST interface. Perstore includes JavaScript object-relational mapping for SQL databases, JSON file storage, and hopefully support for many other object/document style storage systems that provide more direct object storage. Perstore provides model classes that wrap data stores, and supports JSON Schema integrity enforcement, link management, and  prototype construction. Perstore also provides faceted access to models for an object-capability based security model.</p><div class="_0be7a12f f6 black-80 mt1 mb1 flex-ns db flex-row lh-copy"><div class="_045facde flex
